      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Good",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Set in the beautiful world of Dungeonidas, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Knight Witch",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " centres around a group of… knight witches, who are very much the good in this traditional good and evil story. An evil army of golems has taken over Dungeonidas and you control the protagonist Rayne as she defeats the baddies and rescues some kidnapped pals along the way. Rayne is one of the titular ‘knight witches’, which as the name suggests, are a tribe of small mage-witches that whizz around on their brooms. That brings me to my first major positive in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Knight Witch; ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "the traversal and player movement is smoother than a pair of silk pyjamas. As you duck and weave your way through the onslaught of bullets, you find yourself squeezing through the tightest of gaps and it always feels like you’re centimetres from death, but the tight and responsive controls are incredibly satisfying as you slip through at the last second, just like that scene from ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Indiana Jones",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "and the",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Temple of Doom",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ".",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The art style is beautiful and the whole adventure sounds, looks and feels like a 2D ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Legend of Zelda",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " game, which I love. That kind of cutesy style contrasted against a slightly dark and foreboding story really fits well here. I understand that everything in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Knight Witch ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "is hand-drawn and that attention to detail really pays off. I tried playing both portably and on the TV and it was the latter when Dungeonidas really came to life. What a beautiful world to explore!",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "html",
        "html": "<a href=\"https://powera.pxf.io/c/3324894/1258631/15385\" target=\"_top\" id=\"1258631\"><img src=\"//a.impactradius-go.com/display-ad/15385-1258631\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"728\" height=\"90\"/></a><img height=\"0\" width=\"0\" src=\"https://imp.pxf.io/i/3324894/1258631/15385\" style=\"position:absolute;visibility:hidden;\" border=\"0\" />"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "With ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Knight Witch ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "being a metroidvania, there is plenty to do and plenty to find as you explore the world. You are rewarded for having a good old fashioned poke-around and I can’t believe that combining metroidvanias and deck-building games hasn’t been done more frequently. The exploration and secret-finding that a metroidvania encourages is incredibly conducive to a deck-building game because finding more powerful cards of course reaps rewards in combat and other scenarios. So yeah, I wonder if Super Awesome Hyper Dimensional Mega Team have started a new trend, let's see!",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
